    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Eurasian garden and field bird; it gathers in large flocks in the Autumn for migration to northern Africa and the Middle East. The bird's common name is French, from the Latin "hortulanus," meaning the "gardener bird."</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
